<br>
When he had to to, she broke charm, and we killed the monster. It only had 4 pieces left...<br>
<br>
I read somewhere that dire pets take armour differently than mage pets, sure hope this is the case...<br>
<br>
Iblis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umoghedancarns.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moghedan Carns</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/starwars/lightsaber.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#333333>(8/5/02 5:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=617.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~moghedan/pics/littlebelle.jpg hieght=133 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Giving armour to Dire Charmed pet</span><hr size=1> I was still doing tests when I quit and decided it wasn't worth it... the differences were too small to notice, and I could not get THAT precise a varience in the MOBs I was fighting.<br>
<br>
I think pets have two hand slots and 6 anything slots... and that's it.<br>
<br>
I am curious.... were the 4 remaining pieces the first 4 you gave, or the last 4?  That was a varible I needed to nail down before I could figure out the best tests. <p>Moghedan Carns,<BR>
